org.opentosca.toscana.model.requirement

Class Requirement<CapabilityT extends Capability,NodeT extends RootNode,RelationshipT extends RootRelationship>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentosca.toscana.model.BaseToscaElement
      • org.opentosca.toscana.model.requirement.Requirement<CapabilityT,NodeT,RelationshipT>
  • Type Parameters:
    CapabilityT - the Capability Type which is needs to be fulfilled
    NodeT - the Node Type which must be used to fulfill the requirement
    RelationshipT - the Relationship Type which is constructed by fulfilling the requirement
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ApplicationRequirement, BlockStorageRequirement, ContainerHostRequirement, DatabaseEndpointRequirement, DbmsRequirement, Dependency, DockerHostRequirement, HostRequirement, JavaRuntimeRequirement, MysqlDbmsRequirement, NetworkRequirement, StorageRequirement, WebServerRequirement

    public class Requirement<CapabilityT extends Capability,NodeT extends RootNode,RelationshipT extends RootRelationship>
extends BaseToscaElement
    A dependency of a Node which needs to be fulfilled by a matching Capability. The requirement may itself include the specific Node Instance (explicitly) or provide an abstract type, that a TOSCA orchestrator can use to fulfill the capability (implicitly). (TOSCA Simple Profile in YAML Version 1.1, p. 84)
